    "editor": "code",
    "content": "\n                        [p]The atlas is intended as a place to explore and write about your physical locations, \n                        like [tooltip: Use the geography template.]universes, galaxies, solar systems, planets, \n                        continents, islands, mountain ranges, forests, rivers[/tooltip], [tooltip: Use the \n                        settlement template.]cities, ruins[/tooltip], [tooltip: Use the building / landmark template.] \n                        buildings other important landmarks[/tooltip] of your world.[/p]\n                        [p]It might make sense to keep all the locations together in one category, but as you add more locations you should find your own style that works best for you![/p]\n                        [quote]\n                          [h2]Tips & Tricks: Artemis (Quick Navigation)[/h2]\n                            [ol]\n                              [li]Press CTRL + Enter to activate the Artemis quick navigator.[/li]\n                              [li]Write \"edit\" (or just \"e\"), space, and the name of any of your articles to go to the edit page.[/li]\n                              [li]Write \"list\" (or just \"l\"), space, and then \"articles\", \"maps\", \"timelines\" etc. to go to your list of items in less than a second.[/li]\n                            [/ol]\n                        | [user:dimitris]\n                        [/quote]\n                        \n                        [h1]Further Reading[/h1]\n                        [p]Read the Codex (Documentation) Guide to Maps [/p]\n                        [articleblock:3b25efef-3073-4345-a453-476dd12d8fe8]\n                        [h2]Are you looking on how to create a map?[/h2]\n                        Check our [url:https://blog.worldanvil.com/category/mapmaking/]blog articles of Map Making[/url], We have articles about applications and other ways you can use to create the perfect map for you\n                        \n                    ",
